<br>
The RL death of even one person cannot be compared to someone KSing a mob, training someone, or anything that EQ has to offer.  To even think it does trivializes those horrible acts on September 11.  Someone in my guild lost his mother who worked in the WTC on that day.  Please take the time to explain to him how postings on this board or playing EQ compares in any way to how he feels about what happened to his family.  Explain to him how seeing people making quick bucks selling T-Shirts with flags on them and American flags on them by the curb-side makes things better for him.<br>
<br>
I'm by far from indifferent on this.  I see people selling the &quot;patriotic&quot; trinkets, creating &quot;patriotic songs&quot; to sell some records, and promoting sales profitting from something that is one of the worst events that has ever happened.  It's almost like a sorority shirt commemorating the event.  I see people trivializing those events by comparing those events with anything and everything that pops into their head.  I've seen car dealers advertise with references to the terrorist acts.  Those are the people who should check their pulses, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
To say that &quot;All this bickering just seems so damn petty after the events of the last few weeks.&quot; is laughable.  Any bickering about a computer game is petty when compared to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  anything</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  To bring up a comparison between these bickerings and &quot;the events of the last few weeks&quot; lessens those &quot;events of the last few weeks&quot; more than it does strengthen the pettiness of the bickering.   Would you also start calling your house Auschwitz if you found a gas leak in it?<br>
<br>
I won't comment on this thread anymore. <p><P>
